"""
ECG Signal Quality Index (SQI) — 12-Lead Consensus Beat Selection
==================================================================
Supervisor's strategy:
  "When all 12 leads say YES for a beat → include it for training.
   If even ONE lead says a beat is corrupted → exclude that beat
   from ALL 12 leads. This ensures temporal relationships between
   leads are preserved during training."

Bug fixes in this version
──────────────────────────
  FIX 1: IndexError  t[e] out of bounds  → use t[min(e, len(t)-1)]
  FIX 2: NO_STABLE_TEMPLATE for Lead III / aVF (unusual morphology)
          → cross-lead template fallback: borrow template from Lead II
            (or any other lead that successfully built one) and use it
            to score beats in the failing lead.
  FIX 3: aVF different R-peak count (different detector result)
          → consensus alignment uses minimum beat count across leads

Key change from v1
──────────────────
  Previous : each lead independently classified beats
  This code: per-beat CONSENSUS across all 12 leads
             → beat index i is clean ONLY if N_LEADS_REQUIRED leads agree
             → the SAME beat mask is applied to every lead

Usage
─────
  result = run_single_record(mat_path, hea_path)
  mask   = result["consensus_beat_mask"]   # True = use for training
  for ln, beats in result["consensus_clean_beats"].items():
      print(ln, beats.shape)   # (n_clean, win_len) per lead
"""

